obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line 1
  line `THE BENGAL BONDED WAREHOUSE ASSOCIATION ACT, 185 4`
  line `A CT N O. V OF 185 4`
  line `[ Passed on the 1 0 th February, 185 4.]`
  line `1. Repeal ss. 12, 14, 32, and 37, of Act 5 of 1838.`
  line `2. Business to be managed by six Directors, three to be quorum.`
  line `3. Directors to go out of office before annual meeting of May in new election to be made then, and old`
  line `Directors to be re - eligible.`
  line `4. Qualification of Director, 5 shares in his own right.`
  line `5. Ordinary General Meeting to be held twice a year, and when: and ma y declare divide n d, but not`
  line `out of capital.`
  line `6. Empowers Association to make By - laws.`
  line `7. Corporation may be dissolved after 5 years from date of order to that effect, but no such order to`
  line `be made till after 14 th March, 1860.`
  line `An Act to amend Act No. V. of 1838, relating to the Bengal Bonded Warehouse Association.`
  line `W hereas the Bengal Bonded Warehouse Association are desirous that the provision of Act No. V. of`
  line `1838 should be amended, and it appears reasonable that such amendment should be made; It is enacted as`
  line `follows:`
  line `I. Section XII. XIV., XXXII. And XXXVII. Of the said Act are hereby repealed.`
  line `II. The business of the said Association shall be managed by six Directors, three of whom shall from a`
  line quorum.
  line `III. The two Directors who are to go out of office by rotation in every year shall go out of office in`
  line `the month of May, before the holding of the ordinary General Meeting of proprietors directed to be`
  line `ho l den in that month, and at such ordinary General Meeting two Directors shall be chosen, and the`
  line `Directors so going out of office or either of them shall be capable of being re - elected in the same year at`
  line `such General M eeting.`
  line `IV. No person shall be capable of being a Director of the said Association who shall not be a`
  line `proprietor in his own right of Five shares of the Capital Stock of the said Association.`
  line `V. Ordinary General Meetings of the said proprietors shall be held at least twice in every year, that is`
  line `to say, on the second Wednesday in the month of May, and the second Wednesday in the month of`
  line `November, and at every such ordinary Meeting the Directors of the said Association shall present a`
  line `Report in writing of the state of the affairs of the said Association and a balance sheet; and such General`
  line `Meeting may declare a dividend out of the profits of the said Association, provided that no dividend shall`
  line `be made which shall diminish the capital of the said Association.`
  line `VI. It shall be lawful for the said Association to make Bye - laws for the Regulation of its own`
  line `proceedings, which Bye - laws shall be binding only on its own Members and Officers, provided tha t no`
  line `such Bye - law shall be valid till its shall have been approved of by one extraordinary General Meeting of`
  line `proprietors specially convened for that purpose, provided also that no such Bye - law shall be valid till it`
  line `shall have been confirmed by the Govern or of the Presidency of Fort William in Bengal.`
  line `VII. At any time after the 14th day of march 1860, it shall be lawful for the Governor`
  line `General of India in Council by an order in council to direct that the said Association shall be`
  line `dissolved at the expira tion of five years from the date of such order, and such order shall of itself`
  line `have the effect of dissolving the said corporation at the expiration of the said space of five years,`
  line `except for the purposes mentioned in Section XXXIX., Act No. V. of 1838.`
